      "content": "but isn't the \"execution\" argument just a way to delay progress? like, if every other successful country has figured out how to manage the admin costs and still provide care for everyone, isn't it actually more \"factual\" to say universal healthcare works, and that the opposition is just making excuses to keep the profit margins high for private companies? it feels like you're giving equal weight to a proven model and a purely ideological one.",
